# FakeWriter — Implementation Plan

A Windows desktop application that intercepts keystrokes at the OS level and replaces them with pre-defined text, making it look like the user is naturally typing the prepared text.

## Technology Stack

| Component | Technology | Rationale |
|---|---|---|
| Language | **Python 3.10+** | Native Windows API access via `ctypes`, fast development |
| GUI | **customtkinter** | Modern dark-themed UI out of the box, lightweight |
| Keyboard Hook | **ctypes + user32.dll** | Direct `WH_KEYBOARD_LL` hook — full OS-level interception |
| Keystroke Injection | **ctypes + SendInput** | OS-native simulated input, accepted by all apps |
| Foreground Detection | **ctypes + user32.dll** | `GetForegroundWindow` + `GetWindowText` for app targeting |
| Overlay Widget | **tkinter Toplevel** | Transparent, always-on-top floating status widget |

---

